The CRC polynomial used by DDR5 is the ATM-8 HEC, X^8+X^2+X^1+1 that is same as used on DDR4.
A combinatorial logic block implementation of this 8-bit CRC for 64-bits of data contains TBD two-input 
XOR gates contained in eight 6 XOR gate deep trees.
Table 364 shows error detection coverage of DDR5 CRC.
